openadk.library.impl
Class ElementDefImpl

java.lang.Object
  openadk.library.impl.ElementDefImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
ElementDef
Direct Known Subclasses:
ElementDefAlias
public class ElementDefImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements ElementDef

Provides metadata for a single SIF data object type or field (an attribute or child element). This information is used internally by the class framework to parse and render messages.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Eric Petersen

Constructs an ElementDef with flag

Parameters:
parent - The parent of this element
name - The version-independent name of the element
tag - The element or attribute tag (if different from the name)
sequence - The zero-based ordering of this element within its parent or -1 if a top-level element
localPackage - The name of the package where the corresponding DataObject class is defined, excluding the com.edustructures.sifworks prefix
earliestVersion - The earliest version of SIF supported by this element. If the element is supported in any other version of SIF - or is deprecated in a later version - the SDOLibrary class must define it by calling defineVersionInfo

public ElementDefImpl(ElementDef parent,

                      java.lang.String localPackage,
                      int flags,
                      SIFVersion earliestVersion,

Constructs an ElementDef with flag

Parameters:
parent - The parent of this element
name - The version-independent name of the element
tag - The element or attribute tag (if different from the name)
sequence - The zero-based ordering of this element within its parent or -1 if a top-level element
localPackage - The name of the package where the corresponding DataObject class is defined, excluding the com.edustructures.sifworks prefix
flags - One of the following: FD_ATTRIBUTE if this element should be rendered as an attribute of its parent rather than a child element; FD_FIELD if this element is a simple field with no child elements; or FD_OBJECT if this element is a SIF Data Object such as StudentPersonal or an infrastructure message such as SIF_Ack; FD_DEPRECATED if this element no longer applies to this version of SIF
earliestVersion - The earliest version of SIF supported by this element. If the element is supported in any other version of SIF - or is deprecated in a later version - the SDOLibrary class must define it by calling defineVersionInfo

getSDOPath

public java.lang.String getSDOPath()
Description copied from interface: ElementDef
Constructs a path to this ElementDef object, comprised of the names of its ancestry delimited by an underscore. The path can be used to lookup an ElementDef object via the SIFDTD.lookupMetaData method. Note the strings used in the path generated by this method are not necessarily the same as the element or attribute tag names used in SIF XML messages. Rather, they are version-independent names typically equal to the tag name of the element in SIF 1.0r1.

Specified by:
getSDOPath in interface ElementDef
Returns:
A path string (e.g. "StudentPersonal_RefId")

Specified by:
getSQPPath in interface ElementDef

isCollapsed

public boolean isCollapsed(SIFVersion version)
Description copied from interface: ElementDef
Determines if this element should not be written in this version of SIF, but that rather it's children should be written in it's place. This is helpful for cases where a set of elements valid for one version of SIF were moved inside of a new container element in a subsequent version (e.g. StudentPersonal/Email )

Specified by:
isCollapsed in interface ElementDef

True if the element is collapsed in the specified version of SIF

writeObject

public static void writeObject(ElementDef element,
                               java.io.ObjectOutputStream out)
                        throws java.io.IOException
Helper method that can be called from a Serializable class's writeObject method to serialize an ElementDef.

ElementDefImpl is not Serializable, so this method can be called by classes that need to serialize an ElementDef data member. The approach taken is to serialize only the SDO path to the ElementDef. During deserialization, that path is used to lookup the corresponding ElementDef in the ADK.DTD() dictionary. The process that is deserializing the object must have previously initialized the ADK.

Parameters:
element - The ElementDef being serialized
out - The ObjectOutputStream to which the caller is serializing
Throws:
java.io.IOException

readObject

public static ElementDef readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream in)
                             throws java.io.IOException
Helper method that can be called from a Serializable class's readObject method to deserialize an ElementDef.

ElementDefImpl is not Serializable, so this method can be called by classes that need to deserialize an ElementDef data member. The approach taken by the writeObject method is to serialize only the SDO path to the ElementDef. During deserialization, that path is used to lookup the corresponding ElementDef in the ADK.DTD() dictionary. The process that is deserializing the object must have previously initialized the ADK.

Parameters:
in - The ObjectInputStream from which the caller is deserializing
Returns:
An ElementDef
Throws:
java.io.IOException
